OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FInnocent drinks ads banned 
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fover environmental claim   
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Adverts for drinks firm Innocent have  
OL,6, been banned after the advertising      
OL,7, regulator ruled they "misled" customers
OL,8, over the firm's environmental impact.  
OL,10,FInnocent, owned by Coca-Cola, said it  
OL,11,Fwas "disappointed" and had intended to 
OL,12,Fshow "the need for collective action". 
OL,14,FIt comes after Pepsi Lipton and Aqua   
OL,15,FPura water saw ads banned for claims   
OL,16,Fthat their packaging was made from 100%
OL,17,Frecycled materials.                    
OL,19,FInnocent's drinks bottles include      
OL,20,Fnon-recycled plastic.                  
